<div id="review_2686004039" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2686004039" />
    <a title="Heidi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/803808-heidi"><img alt="Heidi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1358206962p2/803808.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2686004039?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heidi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heidi" href="/user/show/803808-heidi">Heidi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2686004039" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5637478623016689650">I picked this out as a classic beginning French book to read/translate with my daughter while we have been living in Paris. It was obviously a little outdated because it was written in the 50s -- Nicholas and his friends are always insulting each other and beating each other up on the playground. Probably is a better book for a 12-year-old boy, but we got a good laugh from the funny scuffles and mischievous antics!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


