<div id="review_3452420925" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3452420925" />
    <a title="Jo Coleman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39966417-jo-coleman"><img alt="Jo Coleman" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1423568844p2/39966417.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3452420925?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jo Coleman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jo Coleman" href="/user/show/39966417-jo-coleman">Jo Coleman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3452420925" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer230124665774323563">Good fun, with excellent plotting of the chaos that can ensue whenever small boys get together and do... pretty much anything. The illustrations are awesome, though unfortunately sometimes they spoilt the punchline of the story by appearing a couple of pages too early. Just about easy enough for me to slog through several dozen years after French A-level, and I learned some key vocabulary about punching people on the nose.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


