<div id="review_2960838936" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2960838936" />
    <a title="Ginny Kestel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64658280-ginny-kestel"><img alt="Ginny Kestel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615918354p2/64658280.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2960838936?book_show_action=true">Oct 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ginny Kestel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ginny Kestel" href="/user/show/64658280-ginny-kestel">Ginny Kestel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2960838936" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8405705762484083218">This was the first book I read in a completely different language: French. It is written for children, but when you’re reading in a language that isn’t your mother tongue, you have to start with something that you can understand without the overwhelming length of a novel with too many words and phrases that ruin the reading experience. The illustrations by Goscinny are a lovely accompaniment to the stories. The book itself is comprised of several chapters that account different stories from the </span>
  <span id="freeText8405705762484083218" style="display:none">This was the first book I read in a completely different language: French. It is written for children, but when you’re reading in a language that isn’t your mother tongue, you have to start with something that you can understand without the overwhelming length of a novel with too many words and phrases that ruin the reading experience. The illustrations by Goscinny are a lovely accompaniment to the stories. The book itself is comprised of several chapters that account different stories from the perspective of the main character Nicolas. The stories were very funny. Reading this in French was extremely helpful in learning new vocabulary and seeing how much I remembered from my high school French classes. I understood about 70% of the text, but of course, I had a French to English dictionary nearby in case I needed to look a word up. One of my new favorite words is “le chouchou” or “the teacher’s pet,” describing the character Agnan. Such a delightful read. If you’re learning French or want to brush up on your skills, I absolutely recommend this.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8405705762484083218" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

